******
[2]
Date: 3 Sep 2011
Source: Infectious Disease Examiner [edited]
http://www.examiner.com/infectious-disease-in-national/zambia-reports-120-human-cases-of-anthrax-from-consuming-infected-hippo


The Zambia Ministry of Health [MoH] reported on Friday [2 Sep 2011]
that 120 people have been infected with anthrax in the Chama district
in Eastern Province.

MoH spokesperson Dr Kamoto Mbewe says all the patients involved in the
outbreak had a history of having consumed or touched infected hippo
meat.

Breeze News reports that senior veterinary officer Arthur Mubolomena
confirmed at least 3 people had died in the outbreak. Dr Mumbolomena
says that suspected anthrax has killed dozens of hippos in Luangwa
River since the outbreak began some 2 weeks ago.

[byline: Robert Herriman]

